      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SIR PANAMA (1) is close to breaking through after three consecutive placings, the latest coming when second over 1500m at Gawler. Should be prominent from the outset and only needs to hold his form to get the job done. KNIGHT DANCER (5) hasn't been able to break through for an extended period but does come through a stronger race with plenty of subsequent winners around him. Finds a more suitable contest and gets a good chance to break a long run of outs. PEERLESS LAD (6) improved last start but found a couple better here. Peaking now and is one of the main winning hopes. AUGUSTA ROCK (2) got too far back here last time but did make some late inroads to finish third. Gets weight relief with the 2kg claimer engaged. Watch for him running on late.",
